<br>
Smiling she unsaddled and brushed off the tired mare and sent her off grazing where she was allowed. More tired than she had been in a very long time, Shey plopped down onto a small chair that sat under her favorite tree and leaned against it's stump. Mud and clay from the rivers streaked her forehead, and water droplets still fell from her leathers, but still she was home again. Proceeding to unload more weight from her weary body, she set the saddlebags she had been carrying onto the ground and opened them to see what she had left. Three swords, two pairs of sais, two carved staves and a chakrum. She was satisfied with her saled and huffed a sigh of relief. It was time to get back to living with her sisters, and the thought of being home with her 'family' again was a happy event that made her want to cry with joy. However, the dirt streaking her face would prevent any such action less it stick further.<br>
<br>
&quot;Clearence sale... Anyone?&quot; She whispered to herself as she laughed.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 455<br> <font color=#993300>(5/14/03 8:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=479.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No rest for the weary</span><hr size=1>  Dawn was a legend, her name brought about the stirrings of stories and memories that not many Amazons shared-of course, that was because Dawnithinia Rivent Darkshade had been much of a misunderstanding to those who never took the chance to understand. It wasn't much of a secret that the Dawn of old days had replaced the one most amazons new, and that Dawn; was back in town.<br>
<br>
 It wasn't much of a change, more than Dawn had returned to her days of being a rogue assassin. In truth, it was probably better for Dawn, easier for all involved. In that sense of being a rogue, Dawn had taken a few days from XVH, and had taken her time travelling back through Amazon lands-finding old sisters whom she thought might have missed her. Along this trail, on the grand afternoon that it was..stallion and assassin stumbled upon Shey.<br>
<br>
 From behind the tree, Dawn dismounted her horse, and like Shey allowed it to graze. Silently, the assassin walked around the tree, resting hand around the hilt of her sword, and the other behind her back. A genuine smile played upon her lips, and those trademark emerald pools glanced downward upon Shey through trendrils of blood.<br>
<br>
 &quot;I don't suppose you're willing to sell an assassin a new dagger.. or two.&quot;<br>
<br>
 The smile turned to a grin, as Dawn waited for Shey to reply. It wouldn't take the amazon long to recognize Dawn; she hadn't changed much, she was still strong, dressed in black, and carried weaponary to state her strength. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sheyala>Sheyala</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#993300>(5/15/03 7:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=479.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> DAWN!!!!!!!!</span><hr size=1> Shey had heard the rustling of the grass, and with a questioning gaze she turned at a familiar voice. What she saw shocked her. It was Dawn.. but it couldn't be.. could it? Without a care her gaze turned into a warm smile, her lips quirking at the sight of such an old friend. She didn't have many of those left.... And without any warning or thoughts of repercussions she threw her arms around the old assassin, hugging her tightly almost as if she was making sure this person wasn't a mirage.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dawn! Could it really be you.... I had thought you...&quot; Thought her what? dead but of course she couldn't bring herself to say it. That word brought a lot of hard times upon her. Too many to count.... &quot;where how when..&quot; She stopped suddenly and laughed at herself. &quot;Of course Sheyala has weapons. Whenever in history has she not?&quot; <br>
<br>
Another voice joined the group. It sounded old and tired, but as blunt and momotonous as always. The great white wolf Anya appeared in Shey's doorway, sitting on her graying haunces. Her silver coat wasn't what it used to be... But her spirit was always young. &gt;&gt;Welcome back assassin.. You smell....as always.&lt;&lt; Another laugh from Shey, another hug. Hopefully it wasn't possible for dawn to suffocate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 457<br> <font color=#993300>(5/18/03 11:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=479.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAWN!!!!!!!!</span><hr size=1>  Dawn, for a moment, hesitated in reaction to Shey's hug, but eventually fell into a response with another hug. It felt good to be around her true athelfi, around those whom had known her, and those whom had missed her.<br>
<br>
 &quot;I had.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Was Dawn's only simple response. There wasn't much more to give, she had been dead, she had been gone, and now she had returned. Of course, with all good returns, was a story.. for another time.<br>
<br>
 &quot;I'm back now. For awhile.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn smiled, giving some sort of support before looking to Anya. The wolf companion had been no surprise, Dawn had sensed her from the beginning..and probably found Shey because of the animal.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Thank you Anya, it feels good to be home.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sheyala>Sheyala</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 471<br> <font color=#993300>(5/19/03 8:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=479.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ^^;</span><hr size=1> Shey smirked as Dawn was taken aback, but had no smart replies to it for now. Ever since her friends had gone, life, even with Anya had been very lonely. <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, well welcome back in any case. I hope it is a long while, but I know better than to ask. Are you hungry or thirsty at all? I just hauled a deer back with me this morning, ready for cooking if you would like some.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, home. Now she could truly call it that. Home was where your friends were. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 460<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/03 8:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=479.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ^^;</span><hr size=1>  &quot;I'm fine. Remember.. I don't eat much.&quot;<br>
