<br>
 Dawn raised a single blonde brow, awaiting response. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sheyala>Sheyala</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 472<br> <font color=#993300>(6/4/03 10:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=479.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gemstone.net/etimes/et5/images/faerie-queen.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No rest for the weary</span><hr size=1> Shey balanced the question in her mind. There were many reasons, some she didn't want to admit and some she wasn't really sure of. Silently she looked from her feet to Anya and back to Dawn.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, there are many reasons I suppose. I have been traveling for a year and a half, and almost didn't make it back. But during my trip I discovered that I am getting to old for that sort of thing Dawn, and Anya isn't getting any younger either. So I returned to settle here for a time to rest up and regain what has been lost or forgotten when I was gone.&quot;<br>
<br>
Anya chuckled to herself. &gt;&gt;You make it sound as if we are falling apart and wasting away. You are not that old...&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Shey chuckled. &quot;No, but you are&quot;<br>
<br>
She refused to mention that she and Anya had been lonely, for they had been alone far before they came to Themiscrya, but ever since finding, and losing friends here, they felt the need to be around anything familiar. <br>
<br>
&quot;So here I am. And what about you?&quot; She raised a brow with a smirk, that old glimmer back in her eyes. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
