<br>
 Why had she come back to the amazon lands?<br>
<br>
 For a few moments Dawn remained silent, rolling the hilt of a dagger between her two hands as she pondered the answers that were more appropriate to give to Shey, and then the answers that her athelfi was more likely to go hunting for-knowing they existed. Then Dawn looked up at Shey, taking a deep breath she prepared her answer and then spoke.<br>
<br>
 &quot;I came back because of my athelfi. I'm not much of an amazon sister anymore, nor do I request that I become like I was. I'm quite happy with the reputation that the Amazon Nation has for me, and carries with it in its stories. But I came back for my athelfi. I came back to check on my daughter whose taken over Orio-Pata, to check on my students who've created their own tribe with a power triad of Queen's.&quot;<br>
